               <msContents class="lemmatic">
                  <summary>This manuscript contains commentary on the book of Aphorisms attributed to <persName type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/287984736" key="person_287984736">Hippocrates</persName>.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Ar_1037-item1">
                     <author key="person_f4928">
                        <name type="supplied" subtype="aut">
                           <persName xml:lang="en">ʿAli bin Ṭāhir al-Ṭabīb al-Sinǧārī</persName>
                           <persName xml:lang="ar">علي بن طاهر الطبيب السنجاري</persName>
                        </name>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_7774">Kitāb Taysīr al-Wuṣūl ʾilā tafsīr al-fuṣūl li-ʾAbuqrāṭ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_7774">Making It Easy to Arrive at an Explanation of Hippocrates’ ‘Aphorisms’</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_7774">كتاب تيسير الوصول إلى تفسير الفصول لأبقراط</title>
                     <note>Original manuscript in Manuscrits de la Fondation Georges et Mathilde Salem.</note>
                     <note>This is a lemmatically arranged commentary. The introduction begins on f. 1b (as <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/76627502" key="person_76627502">Pormann</persName> and <persName key="person_f1772">Joosse</persName> point out, it has a longer version of the introduction); the beginning of each Book is as follows: Bk 1: <locus>2b</locus>; Bk 2: <locus>15a</locus>; Bk 3: <locus>34b</locus>; Bk 4: <locus>50a</locus>; Bk 5: <locus>78b</locus>; Bk 6: <locus>101a</locus>; Bk 7: <locus>116b</locus>.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <author key="person_44576904" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/44576904">Río Sánchez, Francisco del</author>, <title>Catalogue des manuscrits de la fondation Georges et Mathilde Salem (Alep, Syrie)</title>
                           <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="2008">2008</date>, <biblScope unit="volume"/>
                           <biblScope unit="pages">p. 131,</biblScope> no. 235.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
